<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the main economic grievance of farmers that led to the Populist movement?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">High railroad shipping rates</option>
            <option letter="b">Excessive government regulation</option>
            <option letter="c">Labor union strikes</option>
            <option letter="d">Foreign competition</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Farmers faced crippling shipping rates from railroad monopolies, which became a key grievance leading to the formation of the Populist movement.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>The Farmers' Alliance was significant because it:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Won the presidential election of 1892</option>
            <option letter="b">Created a network of cooperative enterprises</option>
            <option letter="c">Supported gold standard policies</option>
            <option letter="d">Opposed women's participation in politics</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Farmers' Alliance created cooperative enterprises to help farmers bypass exploitative middlemen and railroads.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>Which crop led to many farmers' economic difficulties in the 1890s due to overproduction?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Cotton</option>
            <option letter="b">Tobacco</option>
            <option letter="c">Corn</option>
            <option letter="d">Rice</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Cotton overproduction led to falling prices and increased debt for many farmers, especially in the South.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What was the "subtreasury plan" proposed by the Farmers' Alliance?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">A national sales tax</option>
            <option letter="b">A government loan program for farmers</option>
            <option letter="c">A railroad regulation system</option>
            <option letter="d">A farm insurance program</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The subtreasury plan proposed government loans to farmers using their crops as collateral, allowing them to avoid selling at harvest when prices were lowest.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>How did the Farmers' Alliance differ from earlier agricultural organizations?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It was smaller in scope</option>
            <option letter="b">It focused only on social issues</option>
            <option letter="c">It included economic and political goals</option>
            <option letter="d">It excluded Southern farmers</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>The Farmers' Alliance was more comprehensive than earlier farm groups, combining economic cooperation with political reform goals.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
